com.nokia.maps.routing

Interface Maneuver


  • public interface Maneuver
    This interface defines a maneuver, which describes an action that a person needs to perform when following a route. Specifically, a maneuver applies to a particular route link, which is a part of a route calculated by the back-end server, has a server-assigned identifier, and is defined as a set of instances of GeoCoordinate.
    See Also:
    Route
